      <description>&lt;p&gt;Was introduced to &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ashtangayoga.info/practice/basic-sequence-fundamental-positions/item/padangushthasana/&#34;&gt;Padangusthasana&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ashtangayoga.info/practice/basic-sequence-fundamental-positions/item/pada-hastasana/&#34;&gt;Padahastasana&lt;/a&gt; followed by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ashtangayoga.info/practice/basic-sequence-fundamental-positions/item/utthita-trikonasana/&#34;&gt;Trikonasana A&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ashtangayoga.info/practice/basic-sequence-fundamental-positions/item/parivritta-trikonasana/&#34;&gt;Trikonasana B&lt;/a&gt; today. Called for a bit of stability and a lot of focus!&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I seem to have a got a hang of the Sun Salutations. I did catch myself doing a few mistakes, but guess that&amp;rsquo;s good. Was in sync with Miss Me for the most part today and realised I wasn&amp;rsquo;t doing the last three closing sequences quite right&amp;hellip;nuances! Some more practice and it should soon be second nature&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;images/cropped-cropped-SP01-550afdebv1_site_icon.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;  /&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://srikanthperinkulam.com&#34;&gt;Srikanth Perinkulam&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
